title: Scraped Knees Protocol
description:
“Hold still, you insufferable Araneae!”

Spider-Man swung back and forth, dodging large mechanical arms desperately trying to get a hold of him by a hair and occasionally, if he felt cocky, doing little aerial tricks. “C’mon, Doc. You know that’s not how the game works,” he quipped. “You have to catch me. It’d be cheating if I let you, and what fun is that?”

Doc Oct scowled as he tried to out-think the jumping spider in order to catch him. “Are you ever quiet, boy?”

Peter landed on a building’s wall, hand over his heart as he faked being offended. “Excuse me, it’s Spider- Man , not Spider- Boy , Mister Doctor. How dare you?” He jumped out of the way of a few mechanical arms. “And why are you complaining? You’ve got four extra limbs on me, you should be winning!” Webs shot from the spider vigilante’s wrists and tied two of the octopus arms together. “Then again, it also says something about you that despite your advantages, I’m still kind of winning.”

“Shut the hell up!” Octavius screamed. In his rage, the man mechanical arms went into a frenzy. They jutted out and were now flailing wildly. There wasn’t a strategic flow of movements anymore as Doctor Octopus usually had– he was just trying to knock the annoying hero out of his way in any way he could, damaged arms or not.

“Hey, hey, hey!” Peter yelped, barely avoiding the machines. “Watch it! You could really hurt someo–” The wind was then knocked out of him by one of the four arms, sending the Spider-Man flying face-first against the opposite wall. Peter hadn’t had enough time to react to his spidey-sense that attempted to warn him of the oncoming danger, but he had managed to stick his hands out to try and protect his face. It turned out to be a fruitless effort, because not only did Peter still hit his face on a brick that jutted out– more specifically, his right eye and the area around it– but his wrist made a sickening snap sound upon impact.

Peter groaned and moaned as he fell off and onto the ground below, almost seeming the bounce a little as he hit. “Ow…” He knew he should be getting up and trying to web up the doctor, but god, did everything ache.

“Stay out of my way, boy,” Octavius warned, lowering himself down to the ground. “Or next time, I won’t be so merciful.” Peter could hear one of the mechanical octopus arms being raised. “And one more thing– I win. ” With that, he felt a sharp, swift wack to the back of his head, and everything went dark.

body:
Lost way ch.13

A/N-its finally finished! This is last chapter ever. Hope you guys liked it!!

Warning- Spoilers, language

——

Returning the Stones should be easy or at least that’s what I think. Anything could go wrong in time traveling. Which is still something weird for me to hear. I’ve been gone apparently five years and now theirs ways to time travel.

Steve got all the stuff he needed to take the stones back. I asked them if it was possible to bring back Natasha but they said that it was not possible.

“Will you be back?” I ask Steve as he approaches me. He cuped my cheek.

“I just got you back, I’ll be back.” He whispered as he placed a kiss on my forehead. He went to Sam and Bucky and exchanged a few words to them like if he was not coming back. He gave me one more longing kiss before he stepped onto the stand. I crossed my arms over my chest anxiously.

“How long will he take?” I ask Bruce nervously.

“For him as long as he needs for us five seconds.” Bruce answered while he got the machine ready. Steve gave me one last lingering look before he closed his helmet and in a blink of any eye was gone.

It felt like those five seconds took five hours. I waited there and didn’t notice that I was chewing on my nail. I got closer to the stand when Bruce reached five seconds. We were waiting for him but he wasn’t there. I looked over at Bruce and he looked as confused as we were.

“Where is he Bruce?!” Sam asked panicked for his missing friend. Bruce desperately clicked on the buttons.

“I don’t know … I’m trying.” He said.

“Bruce where the hell is he?!” I raised my voice and went over to where he was. I felt my heart beating fast and I fought the urge to cry. I can’t lose him not him too.

“I’m going to try again.” I grabbed the necklace around my neck waiting for anything to happen. I took a deep breath while I heard Bruce count once again to five.

“5…..4…..3…..2…..1” his counting down felt like hours once again. Sam,Bucky and I were by the stand waiting. I felt tears sting my eyes as they threatened to fall when nothing seemed to happen. It was quiet as we waited. The sound of the leaves rustling by the wind was heard and the singing of birds accompanyed it.

The fear of him not coming back was rushing through my head and that’s when he appeared out of nowhere in the same spot he had left. This time he didn’t have a hammer or the stones but he was carrying something. I ran over to him and hugged him.

“I’m sorry something went down while I was returning the stones.” Steve said as he gave me a light kiss on the top of my head.

“Your mission was to return the stuff we took not bring stuff back.” Bruce said as he noticed what Steve was carrying. Steve looked down at his hand. He walked over to Sam and gave him what he was carrying. They walked over to a bench and talked amongst themselves. I stood by Bucky both of us watching the exchange.

I was about to say something to Bucky but the words got caught in my throat when I saw that Steve gave Sam his shield. I was confused at first but I then caught on. I didn’t know if I was sad or happy. They both looked over at us and continued their conversation. They gave eachother a hug and they both finally walked over. Sam gave me a knowing smile as he passed by me.

“I need to talk to you.” Steve said to me in quiet voice. Those words worried me slightly. We moved to the side just of earshot of the guys.

“Are you breaking up with me?” I joked meaning it slightly. He chuckled and grabbed my hand.

“No in fact I want to ask you something and I don’t know if you want to or not but I’ll understand if you don’t.” He took a deep breath and looked into my eyes. I was more confused then before. “I don’t want this anymore…this life I feel like I’ve done my part I completed my mission….. and now that I have, I want to live my life with you I want to build you a house or whatever you want all I know is I want to be done fighting. live that life Tony talked about….finally take that vacation you always wanted.” He cupped my cheeks wiped a tear that ran down my cheek. A smile spread across my face.

“I’d love that….. I love you so much and I wouldn’t want it any other way as long as I’m with you I’m down for anthing…thank you Steve for everything for showing me that I can love again for helping find my way when I had lost it. I love you.”

-

And life was like that they both took their vacation and lived a beautiful life together filled with joy. They lived a simple life after a life of adventure and danger something they both won’t forget. She had finally found her way she was no longer lost ever not with him.

.

.

.

.

.

Steve got all the stuff he needed to take the stones back. I asked them if it was possible to bring back Natasha but they said that it was not possible.

“Will you be back?” I ask Steve as he approaches me. He cuped my cheek.

“I just got you back, I’ll be back.” He whispered as he placed a kiss on my forehead. He went to Sam and Bucky and exchanged a few words to them like if he was not coming back. He gave me one more longing kiss before he stepped onto the stand. I crossed my arms over my chest anxiously.

“How long will he take?” I ask Bruce nervously.

“For him as long as he needs for us five seconds.” Bruce answered while he got the machine ready. Steve gave me one last lingering look before he closed his helmet and in a blink of any eye was gone.

It felt like those five seconds took five hours. I waited there and didn’t notice that I was chewing on my nail. I got closer to the stand when Bruce reached five seconds. We were waiting for him but he wasn’t there. I looked over at Bruce and he looked as confused as we were.

“Where is he Bruce?!” Sam asked panicked for his missing friend. Bruce desperately clicked on the buttons.

“I don’t know … I’m trying.” He said.

“Bruce where the hell is he?!” I raised my voice and went over to where he was. I felt my heart beating fast and I fought the urge to cry. I can’t lose him not him too.

“I’m going to try again.” I grabbed the necklace around my neck waiting for anything to happen. I took a deep breath while I heard Bruce count once again to five.

“5…..4…..3…..2…..1” his counting down felt like hours once again. Sam,Bucky and I were by the stand waiting. I felt tears sting my eyes as they threatened to fall when nothing seemed to happen. It was quiet as we waited. The sound of the leaves rustling by the wind was heard and the singing of birds accompanyed it.

The fear of him not coming back was rushing through my head and that’s when he appeared out of nowhere in the same spot he had left. This time he didn’t have a hammer or the stones but he was carrying something. I ran over to him and hugged him.

“I’m sorry something went down while I was returning the stones.” Steve said as he gave me a light kiss on the top of my head.

“Your mission was to return the stuff we took not bring stuff back.” Bruce said as he noticed what Steve was carrying. Steve looked down at his hand. He walked over to Sam and gave him what he was carrying. They walked over to a bench and talked amongst themselves. I stood by Bucky both of us watching the exchange.

I was about to say something to Bucky but the words got caught in my throat when I saw that Steve gave Sam his shield. I was confused at first but I then caught on. I didn’t know if I was sad or happy. They both looked over at us and continued their conversation. They gave eachother a hug and they both finally walked over. Sam gave me a knowing smile as he passed by me.

“I need to talk to you.” Steve said to me in quiet voice. Those words worried me slightly. We moved to the side just of earshot of the guys.

“Are you breaking up with me?” I joked meaning it slightly. He chuckled and grabbed my hand.

“No in fact I want to ask you something and I don’t know if you want to or not but I’ll understand if you don’t.” He took a deep breath and looked into my eyes. I was more confused then before. “I don’t want this anymore…this life I feel like I’ve done my part I completed my mission….. and now that I have, I want to live my life with you I want to build you a house or whatever you want all I know is I want to be done fighting. live that life Tony talked about….finally take that vacation you always wanted.” He cupped my cheeks wiped a tear that ran down my cheek. A smile spread across my face.

“I’d love that….. I love you so much and I wouldn’t want it any other way as long as I’m with you I’m down for anthing…thank you Steve for everything for showing me that I can love again for helping find my way when I had lost it. I love you.”

-

And life was like that they both took their vacation and lived a beautiful life together filled with joy. They lived a simple life after a life of adventure and danger something they both won’t forget. She had finally found her way she was no longer lost ever not with him.

.

.

.

.

.

blog.name: i-love-tony-stark-3000
blog.title: MCU Lord and Saviour Tony Stark ⎊
blog.description: An Iron Man fan in mourning. Thank you, my darling. We'll all take care of Morgan for you. I love you 3000.

summary: Wait...are we ever gonna see Rhodey again? Please let us see him again. I’m glad we’ll be seeing more of Happy, but if we never...
body:
Wait…are we ever gonna see Rhodey again? Please let us see him again. I’m glad we’ll be seeing more of Happy, but if we never see Rhodey again….that’s just sad. If there’s anyone who deserves his own Disney + show, it’s him. I suppose it would have to be based post Endgame and it would be hard to justify the continued use of the War Machine armour if the guy who built it is no longer around to repair it.

Although, what I’d find interesting is if they had Harley Keener come into the picture as the new engineer for the armours and gradually have Rhodey lead Harley towards becoming the new Iron Man or whatever it is he wanted to call himself. Rhodey has got to be nearing 60 by Endgame, so perhaps he could retire from War Machine, but stick around as Harley’s mentor.
